  "prompt": "What is GRE? How can I prepare for it?",
  "response": "The GRE (Graduate Record Examination) is a standardized test required for admission to many graduate schools in the United States and other countries.\n\nHere's a comprehensive guide to preparing for the GRE:\n\n1. Test Structure\n- Analytical Writing (1 essay)\n- Verbal Reasoning (2 sections)\n- Quantitative Reasoning (2 sections)\n- Total test duration: About 3 hours and 45 minutes\n\n2. Preparation Strategies\na) Study Materials\n- Official GRE guide\n- Kaplan/Princeton Review books\n- Online resources\n- ETS official practice tests\n\nb) Study Schedule\n- Create a structured study plan\n- Allocate 2-3 months for preparation\n- Practice regularly\n\n3. Specific Section Preparation\na) Verbal Reasoning\n- Build vocabulary\n- Practice reading comprehension\n- Learn question types\n- Use flashcards\n\nb) Quantitative Reasoning\n- Review math fundamentals\n- Practice problem-solving\n- Learn time management\n- Use calculator strategically\n\nc) Analytical Writing\n- Practice essay writing\n- Learn argument analysis\n- Study sample essays\n- Time yourself\n\n4. Additional Tips\n- Take diagnostic tests\n- Identify weak areas\n- Use online practice platforms\n- Consider GRE prep courses\n- Manage test anxiety\n- Get enough sleep before exam",
